The paper deals with algorithmic fairness in machine learning, specifically in the context of regression problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic classification, which is a common technique in cryptography and security (cs.CR), and the paper also involves the estimation of conditional probabilities, which is a common topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
